---
/**
 * Why soo many icons?
 * 1. The SVG icon is used for modern browsers. It scales automatically and is an adaptive icon based on the user's light/dark mode.
 * 2. The PNG icon is a fallback for browsers that still don't support the SVG icons.
 * 3. The ICO icon is a fallback for older browsers or tools that only support ICO files.
 * 4. The Apple touch icon is used when the page is added as a shortcut to the home screen on an iPhone or iPad.
 */
---

<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg">
<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png">
<link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/icon-180.png">
